Adam Savage's First Look at the EufyMake E1: https://youtu.be/SD8r1UBwLL0

Adam has always loved the look and feel of metal machine labels affixed to his old shop tools, and has never been satisfied with laser cut plastic labels that simulate the vintage look. Using his pantograph mill and the EufyMake EI UV printer, Adam designs and prototypes a set of machine labels that finally lives up to the weathered and tactile aesthetic he's been in search for. 

Shot by Joey Fameli and edited by Norman Chan
Music by Jinglepunks
